Interface InvokedProcessServicer

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

public interface InvokedProcessServicer

             java.lang.Object parameter,
             ManagedObject managedObject)
      throws java.lang.Throwable
        Services the invoked ProcessState.
        Parameters:
        processIndex - Index of the invoked ProcessState. Allows re-using the InvokedProcessServicer for multiple invocations.
        parameter - Parameter to the initial ManagedFunction within the ProcessState.
        managedObject - ManagedObject provided for the invoked ProcessState.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable - If failure on servicing.
